@blurhy:
Do you want to begin a service that ZeroNet needs?
I have something to share to you about it.

ZeroNet, CJDNS and any other open-source project are a problem for who manages the world's enterprises.

Gov, ICANN, ISPs and other tech companies, they don't want open-source projects being merged, receiving and using lots of donations and developers doing a quick and good work without backdoors/security breaches.

What is needed (not by us):
* ZeroNet slow, not supporting IPv6/DHT and not using the donations;
* [CJDNS with no page on Wikipedia](https://www.reddit.com/r/cjdns/comments/83tfoa/reason_triumphs_again_cjdns_deleted_from_wikipedia/), hard to use and [not discoverable by newbie users](https://github.com/tomeshnet/prototype-cjdns-pi/issues/210);
* Namecoin (centralized) as the only domain system on ZeroNet;
* ZeroNet's zites abandoned or with slow development;

But how enterprises haves the power to come to developers and say "don't do it"?
